captions.text:
Gotta find a picture of me
looking cute when I was you--
- Excuse me Miss, are you okay?
Those sidewalks can really get you.
- Alrighty, thank you for your concern.

(sighs) At least no
one I know saw me trip.

Quinta we know you and
we saw you trip. (laughs)
Everyone trips every once in a while.
You looked stupid when you tripped.

Good thing nobody I
cared about saw me trip.
My crush from the third grade?

- Came here to tell you
how much I love you,
- But Chad Dillon I love you.
- I'm goin' to the mall with my jacket.

At least no one who can
pick on me saw me fall.

Brent Blocker, my bully
from the third grade?
- Yeah, I saw you trip Four Eyes.
- I wore glasses in high school.

At least no one who can tell
anybody else saw me trip.

- I just wish someone who
loved me unconditionally
- I used to love you unconditionally.
- But that's before I saw you trip.

All your accomplishments,
degree in physics,

radiant smile, which you
get from your mother,

sparkling sense of humor,
which you get from me.
- What could be worse than this?

respective cars on an early morning donut run. Unfortunately being early, 
dark, and me not watching where I was going, I tripped on this flap of wood 
that normally would sit lodged between the sidewalk panels and I ended up 
tripping and running straight into a concrete pillar. It made so much noise 
me hitting this thing and the wood thwacking back on the concrete. It was 
embarrassing but I just burst out laughing at myself as I tend to do, and 
looked back and the guy was looking like wtf is wrong with you.﻿
